FBIS4-38365 "drsov104_a_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Paper Claims Ames Still Working in Russian Intelligence Paper Claims Ames Still Working in Russian Intelligence LD2805130694 Moscow Ostankino Television Network in Russian 1100 GMT 28 May 94 LD2805130694 Moscow Ostankino Television Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] According to an Ima-press report, LITERATURNAYA GAZETA has sensational materials at its disposal that testify to the fact that Aldridge Ames, who was recently sentenced for spying in the United States, has been handed over to a high-ranking member of staff in Russia's external intelligence service. According to the same source, that double agent still remains in his post in the department of Yevgeniy Primakov. It is expected that he will be exposed in the next few days.
